  "texts": [
    "Here are a few case studies showcasing how lightweight cryptography is applied in various IoT applications: Smart Home Security: Lightweight cryptography is used in a smart home security system to encrypt data sent between various Internet of Things gadgets including smart locks, security cameras, and doorbell cameras.",
    "These gadgets often have little memory and processing capabilities.",
    "To provide safe remote access and data sharing, devices use lightweight cryptographic methods.",
    "IIoT (Industrial IoT):In an industrial IoT setting, where sensors and actuators are placed in factories and supply chains, lightweight cryptography is vital for ensuring the confidentiality and integrity of data.",
    "The safe and effective functioning of industrial processes is ensured by using lightweight algorithms to safeguard data transfer and control systems."
  ],
